\begin{abstract}

Web applications are an extremely important and ubiquitous part of today's world. Students must not only know how to develop web applications from a technical perspective, but also need to understand how to follow the proper principles of Software\dan{Web?} Engineering in order to deliver the project in an on time, on budget and high quality manner.

At the Department of Software Engineering at \ifisnopii the Rochester Institute of Technology\else xxxxxx\fi, we created a course in Web Engineering which is comprised of a significant project component that requires students to use a variety of contemporary technologies and resources in order to create a robust web application in multiple releases using proper Web Engineering principles.

This innovative project component has received significant praise from both students and faculty members while filling a gap in our curriculum. Student enjoy the real-world nature of the project and the ability to work with contemporary technologies in a format which closely mimics what they will see in industry. This paper outlines the educational objectives and project details. The goal of this work is to share the project, its importance, and lessons learned for use at other institutions.

