The Web Engineering course has been offered at \ifisnopii RIT \else xxxxxx \fi for three years, with the goal of this course being to instruct students in how to properly apply software engineering principles in the creation of web applications. This is not just a programming course just like a software engineering course is not a programming course. However, specific technologies and concepts including JQuery, Web Services and security are discussed and introduced with the goal of students leveraging these technologies in their projects. Students were primarily evaluated on their comprehension of engineering principles and not the specific technologies or their programming. We chose to offer our course using the Microsoft .Net framework as a web technology, although we expect other institutions to select the technology of their preference.

The students taking the course were primarily upper-level software engineering students and had a reasonably high level of development experience. Some of the students were generally very experienced with web development while an equal portion had little or no exposure. Some of the biggest emphasized ares include customer elicitation skills, requirements documentation and acceptance testing.

